r jail term for any convict. The Magistrate, Mrs M. I. Dan-Oni, granted the trio bail in the sum of N100, 000 each with two sureties each in like sum and adjourned the case until Feb. 24 for mention. [NAN] Vanguard News Nigeria. A 26-year-old man, Taiwo Fatoki,  on Monday appeared before an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court for allegedly stealing  a a tricycle worth N650,000. October 7, 2019 In "News" A 28-year-old year old man, Segun Sunday, was yesterday brought before an Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court for allegedly stealing his co-worker’s tricycle worth N1.1million. February 14, 2019 In "News" Sunday Ukudolo, a driver, was on Tuesday arraigned before an Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court, for allegedly damaging a perimeter fence and stealing property worth N930,000. Ukudolo, 40, who resides at No. 8, Ugbodu Junction, AP Road, Ikorodu, Lagos State, is being tried for conspiracy, damage and stealing, offences he denied… February 4, 2020 In "Metro"